==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*saxan, *saksan'', from Indo-European ''*sek-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[sax]], Old High German [[sahs]], Old Norse [[sax]].  Compare Old English [[sagu]], [[secg]]. 

